Request active/historic administrative calls data

Source: R/get_admin_calls.R
get_admin_calls.Rd

Request active/historic administrative calls data

Usage

get_admin_calls(
  active = TRUE,
  min_division = NULL,
  max_division = NULL,
  location_wdid = NULL,
  call_number = NULL,
  start_date = "1900-01-01",
  end_date = Sys.Date(),
  api_key = NULL
)

Arguments

active

logical, whether to get active or historical administrative calls. Default iS TRUE and will retrieve active administrative calls.

min_division

numeric, minimum division number to get administrative calls for. Default is 1.

max_division

numeric, maximum division number to get administrative calls for. Default is 7.

location_wdid

numeric, call location structure WDID

call_number

numeric, unique call identifier

start_date

character date to request data start point YYYY-MM-DD

end_date

character date to request data end point YYYY-MM-DD

api_key

character, optional. If more than maximum number of requests per day is desired, an API key can be obtained from CDSS.

Value

dataframe of administrative calls

Examples

# Retrieve ACTIVE administrative calls
active_calls <- get_admin_calls(
               active        = TRUE,
               min_division  = 1,
           )
